The first chest CT scan was performed 1-5 days (3.2 ± 1.3) after the onset of symptoms. Two cases were negative according to the first CT and were positive on the second/follow-up CT. A total of 46 lesions were analysed on the initial positive chest CT. All lobes of the lung can be involved, and the affected segments were located in the lower lobes (54.35% [25/46]) and in the right lobe (56.52% [26/46]) (Table 2
, Fig. 1
). A difference was observed between the sizes of the lesions (5-60 mm). A higher proportion of medium lesions (diameter, 1 to <3 cm) was noted (60.87% [28/46]), and five lesions had sizes less than 10 mm (10.87%% [5/46]) (Fig. 2
, Table 3
).
